gut, what is leaky gut.

1681
01:13:14,350 --> 01:13:16,230
Here, we're talking about the guts,

1682
01:13:16,230 --> 01:13:17,890
what is it to have a leaky
gut, it sounds awful.

1683
01:13:17,890 --> 01:13:20,440
It sounds like something sort
of like leaking out the end

1684
01:13:20,440 --> 01:13:22,500
of the tube, and it maybe
that too, I don't know.

1685
01:13:22,500 --> 01:13:27,500
But leaky gut is actually
because, your gut is not a tube

1686
01:13:27,510 --> 01:13:30,180
that's continuous, one
cell it's actually made up

1687
01:13:30,180 --> 01:13:33,950
of many cells and those
cells form a barrier

1688
01:13:33,950 --> 01:13:36,310
and they form what are
called tight junctions.

1689
01:13:36,310 --> 01:13:38,870
If you have two cells and you
want to create a fence out

1690
01:13:38,870 --> 01:13:40,900
of those cells, you bind them together.

1691
01:13:40,900 --> 01:13:43,160
The way that the body does
this is to bind them together

1692
01:13:43,160 --> 01:13:45,010
with what are called tight
junctions, these are,

1693
01:13:45,010 --> 01:13:47,120
they go by names like
claudins and things like that,

1694
01:13:47,120 --> 01:13:48,230
if you want to look them up.

1695
01:13:48,230 --> 01:13:50,870
These tight junctions form a nice barrier,

1696
01:13:50,870 --> 01:13:53,780
like a cyclone fence, that
things can't get past,

1697
01:13:53,780 --> 01:13:56,970
but like a cyclone fence only
molecules of a certain size

1698
01:13:56,970 --> 01:13:58,635
